column14: TODAYS MMNT COMPLETED APPROX 30m D/S OF FEB 2024 MMNT (AND APPROX 300m D/S OF GAUGE). column14: @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (2 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.ft File). @ **QAQC NOTE - DURING PROCESSING OF DATA FROM FT2 - IT WAS NOTED THAT FT2 CLOCK WAS AHEAD BY 15MIN - BARMSTRONG ADJUSTED START TIME AND END TIME OF MMNT IN eHSN TO CORRECT FOR THIS ISSUE. INCORRECT START AND END TIMES ARE HOWEVER RETAINED ON THE FT2 SUMMARY PRINT OUT. CALCULATION OF cMGH IS NOT IMPACTED AS DWL COLLECTED @ 1725 IS BEING USED AS MGH FOR THIS MMNT. (START TIME ADJUSTED TO 16:02 FROM 16:17, END TIME ADJUSTED TO 17:40 FROM 17:55) TANK CHANGE COMPLETE BY 15:38,   INITIAL WATER LEVEL AT 1520 READ ON LEVEL BUDDY, OLD OFFSET =3.095 NEW OFFSET 3.104, THIS DWL WAS COLLECTED FROM A SETUP ON THE BRIDGE. THE PRISM AND LEVEL BUDDY WAS SETUP JUST  U/S OF WHERE GAUGE POOL EXISTS  COMPLETED  TWO MORE DWL CIRCUITS AND WAS GETTING 3.456 (FOUND HG FROM BEGINNING OF VISIT) EVEN THOUGH ONLY A LESS THAN OR EQUAL TOO 0.003m FLUCUATION WAS SEEN IN THE LOG DATA BETWEEN FIRST RESET @ 1545 AND 2ND/3RD DWLs. WAS ABLE TO REPLICATE THIS DWL OVER A 20 MIN SPAN. PUT IN OLD OFFSET TO REALIGN WITH DWL FROM 1725 AND 1745 PRIOR TO DEPARTING. DURING THESE DWLs, THE SET UP WAS ADJACENT TO THE GAUGE AND THE BUDDY WAS SET UP BOTH TIMES MORE IN LINE WITH THE GAUGE POOL. TECHS FEEL THE 1725/1745 DWLs ARE MORE REPRESENTATIVE THAN WHAT WAS AQUIRED AT 1520 BASED ON SITE CONDITIONS.  RFT - PLEASE DO NOT APPLY A SRC BETWEEN THE LAST VISIT AND THE FIRST DWL AT 1520. 2ND DWL AQUIRED DURING MMNT THEREFORE 3.465m WILL BE USED AS MEAN GAUGE HEIGHT.  Mid-section
